In order to use our ready dataset we had to resize and normalize it.¶

We also generated different versions of them by using random mirroring in parts of the image. This was done to both models and real images.¶

In [ ]:

We then needed to create the generator and discriminator parts for our AI. We used downsampling and upsampling methods in the generator's network, while we just downsampled in the discriminator. This is what we got out of it:¶

Sample output¶

In [ ]:
gen_output = generator(inp[tf.newaxis, ...], training=False)
plt.imshow(gen_output[0, ...])
